    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MOODY'S UPGRADES BRAZIL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Moody's Investors Service raises foreign currency rating on Brazil's bonds and notes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a move that could help reassure skeptical investors, Moody's Investors Service upgraded Brazil's credit rating less than two years after an international financial crisis led to a 40 percent currency devaluation. Moody's said it had raised the foreign currency rating on bonds and notes to B1 from B2. The upgrade, which had been expected, could help lower the country's international borrowing costs.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
